Nicole Gallego", "risk": "Just contacted by rep; senior IT authority and a potential path to power, not yet engaged", "role": "Decision Maker", "title": "Senior VP, Delivery Operations & Information Technology", "sentiment": "unknown", "last_contact_date": "2026-06-26"}, {"name": "Andy Simmons", "risk": "Silent since 30 May; has not introduced the EB or confirmed next steps; project chokepoint", "role": "Champion", "title": "Senior Director Procurement", "sentiment": "positive but cooling", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-30"}, {"name": "Ida Stark", "risk": "AP user; asked for payment-runs / Smartdesk deep dive; user-level advocate not a decision maker", "role": "Influencer", "title": "Conga AP (Financial Operations)", "sentiment": "engaged", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-06"}, {"name": "Jordan Weinberg", "risk": "Low\u2014operational stakeholder, no decision authority.", "role": "Influencer", "title": "Role unclear (attendee on demo)", "sentiment": "Neutral\u2014attendee on demo 2026-05-06, asked technical questions on sourcing and CLM integration. No engagement since (55 days ago).", "last_contact_date": "2026-05-06"}]}, "meddpicc": {"metrics": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma intro call 12 Dec 2025 (Andy Simmons)", "SF Next Step log"], "narrative": "Andy Simmons articulated rich qualitative pain on the 12 Dec intro call but never quantified it: 'we only use NetSuite... shoehorned NetSuite into a procure-to-pay... not a lot of emphasis on sourcing.' Core driver is a 'singular front door' for intake (today via scattered email and Teams) plus standing up a sourcing practice the company does not have at all. No cost, headcount, cycle-time, or savings baseline exists, so there is no ROI model behind the $150K \u2014 a real exposure now that the PROS acquisition (closed ~1 Feb) puts spend under scrutiny. Move: co-build a quantified case (manual-intake cost, sourcing-savings target, AP cycle-time) Andy can carry to the budget owner."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["RFP Invitation 13 Apr 2026 (Andy Simmons)", "Avoma intro 12 Dec 2025", "SF Next Step 30 May / 15 Jun"], "narrative": "Andy is a developing champion who authored and issued the RFP, invited Zycus in writing, shaped criteria around Zycus strengths (full suite, Teams UI, AI negotiation), and brought procurement, AP, and IT to the demo. What is missing and now at risk: he has gone quiet since 30 May, never confirmed the integration call or the live NetSuite offer, and never introduced the economic buyer. His advocacy is real but unproven at the power level. Because he owns the spec, he is the path to the budget owner \u2014 re-arm him, do not route around him."}, "competition": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma intro 12 Dec 2025 (Andy Simmons)", "Avoma demo 6 May 2026"], "narrative": "Andy said Zycus is 'amongst a few other players' but never named the shortlist. The clearest current rival is the status quo \u2014 NetSuite-only manual P2P \u2014 which becomes the realistic outcome if post-acquisition budget tightens. Coupa and Zip surface only from Andy's own usage history (Coupa at prior roles, Zip at Procore), not as confirmed bidders; the Ivalua/Coupa sighting on 17 Mar belongs to a different (BakerRipley) RFP and is not weighted. Wedge: Zycus is the only full intake-to-pay suite with native Teams UI and direct vendor-delivered implementation \u2014 fitting Conga's IT staffing gap. Proving NetSuite integration depth live is how we convert the wedge."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma intro call 12 Dec 2025 (Andy Simmons)", "Avoma demo 6 May 2026 (Ida Stark)"], "narrative": "Pain is concrete and owned by Andy, the new Sr Director of Procurement hired to modernize the function: NetSuite shoehorned into P2P with no real sourcing; chaotic intake via 'email, Teams, or just meetings'; need for 'one singular front door... normalized data flowing through.' AP intake is manual drag-and-drop into MineralTree (Ida Stark, 6 May). Compounding constraint: 'our IT team went through a massive rift earlier this year,' so Conga needs Zycus to own deployment. Post-PROS scaling magnifies the manual-process strain."}, "paper_process": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Email 14 Jan 2026 (executed NDA)", "Avoma demo 6 May 2026", "SF tasks 8-14 May 2026 (pricing input form)"], "narrative": "Contracting mechanics are early. Mutual NDA signed in January. Implementation is Zycus-delivered, not partner-led ('Zycus implements Zycus') \u2014 a fit given Conga's IT rift. A phased 12-20 week plan was agreed on 6 May, but the buyer never returned the user-count input form needed to firm pricing, so no quote, MSA/Order Form, legal, or InfoSec review has started. The path to paper runs through pricing finalization and the unscheduled integration scoping call \u2014 both currently stalled on the buyer."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma intro call 12 Dec 2025 (Andy Simmons)", "Avoma demo 6 May 2026", "SF Next Step 26 Jun"], "narrative": "No economic buyer mapped or engaged in 6.5 months. Andy said on 12 Dec he has 'a lot of people behind this up to the C-level' and 'I'm not doing this on my own,' and the 6 May demo confirmed a CFO sits in the approval chain ('anything above $1,000 goes to you and the CFO'), but that person is unnamed and unengaged. The 26 Jun outreach to Nicole Gallego (SVP Delivery Ops & IT) is the first reach toward a more senior buyer. Because Andy authored the RFP, the path to power runs THROUGH him (or through Nicole if she engages) \u2014 broker the introduction, do not cold-outreach a CFO. This is the single highest-leverage gap and the reason Best Case cannot stand."}, "decision_process": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["SF Next Step log", "RFP Invitation 13 Apr 2026", "Avoma demo 6 May 2026"], "narrative": "Process is readable: NDA signed (Jan), 45-question RFP issued 13 Apr with a concurrent-demo format, response submitted ~29 Apr, demo 6 May, integration/im